tldr: The user requested to add a database, admin dashboard, and authentication
  to a sleep questionnaire application. I developed a plan, implemented the
  features including a PostgreSQL database with Prisma, a simple
  password-protected admin dashboard with CSV export, and refined the
  authentication using Next.js middleware. All core functionalities were
  successfully tested and committed.
overview: The project involved enhancing a sleep questionnaire application by
  integrating a robust data storage solution and an administrative interface.
  The user's intent was to store questionnaire responses, provide a client
  dashboard for data access, and secure it with authentication. The approach
  taken involved using Prisma with a PostgreSQL database (NeonDB) for efficient
  data management. A  model was created to store both raw
  questionnaire data and denormalized demographic information. For the admin
  dashboard, a simple password-based authentication system was implemented using
  Next.js middleware to protect routes and manage user sessions. API endpoints
  were developed for saving questionnaire submissions, retrieving all responses,
  and exporting data as a CSV file. The questionnaire form was updated to submit
  data to the new API. During testing, all core functionalities, including
  database interaction, authentication, and data export, were verified to be
  working correctly. The implementation was then committed in atomic, logical
  steps.
